{"id":"int-c8ed09ce","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T16:31:24.716799943Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-udv","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in ferrum-lang-types.md: as to a constrained target now panics on violation in all build modes. Decision rationale documented inline at both the conversion example and the constraint-checking rule."}}
{"id":"int-b8211ac7","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T16:39:14.278279292Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-lx5","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in ferrum-introduction-to-effects.md: @pure is now compiler-verified, valid only when inferred effects are a subset of {Alloc, Sync}. IO, Net, Panic, Unsafe, Async cannot be suppressed — they are compile errors. Design decision and limitation (correctness of caching logic) documented inline."}}
{"id":"int-b0ca1d03","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T17:00:40.472820587Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-8hw","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in ferrum-lang-verification.md (§3.3) and ferrum-lang-concurrency.md (§1.10). trusted is now prohibited from asserting Send/Sync on types with \\!Sync fields — compile error. The compiler's structural \\!Sync determination cannot be overridden by trusted. Legitimate use case (implementing a custom sync primitive) redirected to unsafe impl Sync. Design decision documented inline."}}
{"id":"int-c6b0b4e8","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T17:06:50.435707572Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-3uu","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in ferrum-lang-syntax.md (§1.6) and ferrum-introduction-to-option-result.md. ? does not coerce via From. Error union (E1 | E2 | ...) is the primary model: compiler infers the union from ? expressions in the body. Private functions use Result[T, _] for inference; pub functions write the union explicitly. Explicit .map_err() is used when collapsing to a named type. Design decision documented inline in syntax spec."}}
{"id":"int-34d7cab5","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T17:28:56.790690876Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-e2j","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in ferrum-lang-generics.md (§1.5) and ferrum-lang-concurrency.md (§1.2). Allocator provenance is now always tracked internally by the compiler, same model as region inference. Surface type Vec[i32] hides the allocator; Vec[i32, Arena] or Vec[i32, _] surfaces it. Spawn safety checks both Send and allocator provenance: scoped-allocator values cannot be captured by tasks that outlive the allocator. Heap-allocated values are always movable. Design decision and error message form documented inline."}}
{"id":"int-eb0b4bee","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T18:02:35.093140142Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-0q0","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed in ferrum-lang-syntax.md (defer added as a first-class block-exit expression) and ferrum-lang-verification.md (§1.4 updated). Invariants now checked at two points: public API boundaries AND exit of trusted/unchecked blocks holding &mut T. Lint mut_invariant_unguarded_exit warns when a trusted block has unguarded early exits on a &mut with invariants. Ownership principle documented: functions that cannot guarantee restoration should take ownership, not &mut."}}
{"id":"int-79d59fd6","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-04-12T18:10:02.951398904Z","actor":"Mark Atwood","issue_id":"FrontierProgrammingLanguageIdeas-5k6","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"Fixed across ferrum-lang-verification.md (§1.9), ferrum-introduction-for-rust-programmers.md, ferrum-introduction-for-haskell-programmers.md, and ferrum-learning-for-ai.md. verified_by split into tested_by (debug-mode runtime comparison, honest about coverage limits) and proven_by (formal compile-time proof, covers all inputs). Both still check signature compatibility as a minimum. Design decision documented inline in verification spec."}}
